  "prompt": "Create an Arduino project named “Servo + LEDs Power-Aware Demo”.\n\nGoals:\n- 1 servo sweeps between 0° and 180°.\n- 3 LEDs indicate position zones (left/center/right).\n- Include a pushbutton to pause/resume motion.\n\nSafety and power constraints:\n- Servo must use an external 5V supply, not Arduino 5V pin.\n- Common ground between Arduino and external supply is required.\n- LED current must stay within safe per-pin limits (use 220Ω resistors).\n- Never power multiple loads from one signal pin.\n- Add a short warning if wiring is unsafe and auto-correct the plan.\n\nDeliverables:\n1) Clear wiring table (component, power source, Arduino pin, notes),\n2) Arduino code with comments,\n3) Power budget summary (per pin + total),\n4) “What can go wrong” checklist for beginners.\n\nKeep implementation beginner-friendly and avoid unnecessary complexity.",
